  "analysis": "## Asterisk Character Analysis\n\n### Character Reading\n\nThis is not a monospace text asterisk — it is a fully 3D-rendered, extruded asterisk glyph used as a logo/icon mark. It reads clearly as an asterisk (six-armed radial form), not as a snowflake. The six arms are evenly distributed at 60-degree intervals, which is the standard asterisk geometry. There is no risk of confusion with a snowflake, plus sign, or cross — the diagonal arms are present and clearly legible.\n\n### Appearance at Small Sizes\n\nAt the size shown (large, icon-scale), the form reads well. However, this is a complex 3D render with beveled edges, specular highlights, and ambient occlusion shadows. At small sizes (e.g., 16px–32px), the following problems would emerge:\n\n- The dark shadowed faces on the left/rear arms would merge into the black background, causing those arms to visually disappear\n- The beveled edges and extrusion depth would become indistinguishable noise\n- The overall silhouette would still read as an asterisk, but the 3D quality would be completely lost and the form may look muddy or uneven\n\nIt is not suitable as a favicon or small UI icon without a flat fallback.\n\n### Surface Treatment / Extrusion Quality\n\nThe extrusion is largely clean with a few notable observations:\n\n- The teal-to-mint gradient on the front-facing surfaces is smooth and well-rendered\n- The specular highlight on the top face of the uppermost arm is bright and clean\n- **Artifact concern:** the top arm has a noticeably rough, granular texture on its top face — it appears almost like a noise or roughness map artifact, inconsistent with the otherwise smooth surfaces on the other arms. This stands out as a flaw.\n- The intersection/center of the arms shows some geometry complexity but reads acceptably at this scale\n- The rear/left arms are very dark and lose definition against the background, which is a compositional weakness rather than a render artifact per se\n- The ambient rim glow (teal/green subsurface-style emission) is consistent and clean around the base\n\n**Summary:** The form is recognizable and well-composed overall, but the rough texture artifact on the top face and the near-invisible dark rear arms are legitimate quality concerns.",
