Yes, DeepSeek V4 Pro is supported. Here's the complete picture.

## All available DeepSeek text models

| Model ID | Name | Max Context | Popularity | Config inputs |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `deepseek-v4-pro` | DeepSeek V4 Pro | 384,000 | 0.3 | reasoning_effort, top_p, top_k, seed, penalties |
| `deepseek-v4-flash` | DeepSeek V4 Flash | 384,000 | 0.4 | reasoning_effort, top_p, top_k, seed, penalties |
| `deepseek-v3-1` | DeepSeek V3.1 | 8,000 | **0.7** | none |
| `deepseek-v3-2` | DeepSeek V3.2 | 8,000 | 0.4 | none |
| `deepseek-chat-deepinfra` | DeepSeek-V3 | 8,000 | 0.5 | none |
| `deepseek-reasoner` | DeepSeek-R1 | 8,000 | 0.5 | none |
| `deepseek-r1-turbo` | DeepSeek R1 Turbo | 8,000 | 0.2 | none |
| `deepseek-chat` | DeepSeek-V3 | 8,000 | 0.2 | none |

---

## Critical heads-up about your credit-reduction goal

**DeepSeek V4 Pro defaults to `reasoning_effort: "high"`** — meaning it runs extended thinking on every call by default. If you swap from `claude-4-6-sonnet` without setting `reasoning_effort: "none"`, you may end up spending *more* credits, not less. The reasoning tokens all count against the 384k context window and bill accordingly.

**To actually reduce costs, pick based on your use case:**

- **General text generation (no reasoning needed):** Use `deepseek-v3-1` — highest platform popularity (0.7), no reasoning overhead, dead simple config. This is your cheapest drop-in swap.
- **Complex tasks that benefit from reasoning, but want control over cost:** Use `deepseek-v4-flash` with `reasoning_effort: "none"` for fast/cheap calls, or `"high"`/`"max"` when you actually need it.
- **You specifically want V4 Pro tier:** `deepseek-v4-pro` — same reasoning controls, just the heavier variant.

---

## Code examples

### Option A — Cheapest swap (DeepSeek V3.1, no reasoning overhead)
```typescript
import { mindstudio, MindStudioError } from '@mindstudio-ai/agent';

try {
  const { content } = await mindstudio.generateText({
    message: 'Your prompt here',
    modelOverride: {
      model: 'deepseek-v3-1', // DeepSeek V3.1 — highest usage DeepSeek model, no reasoning overhead
      temperature: 0.7,
      maxResponseTokens: 8000, // do not reduce — this is the model's full context limit
    },
  });
  console.log(content);
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof MindStudioError) {
    console.error(err.code, err.status, err.message);
  }
  throw err;
}
```

### Option B — DeepSeek V4 Pro with reasoning disabled (cost-controlled)
```typescript
import { mindstudio, MindStudioError } from '@mindstudio-ai/agent';

try {
  const { content } = await mindstudio.generateText({
    message: 'Your prompt here',
    modelOverride: {
      model: 'deepseek-v4-pro', // DeepSeek V4 Pro — 384k context window
      temperature: 0.7,
      maxResponseTokens: 16000, // do not reduce — reasoning tokens count against this; model stops on its own when done
      config: {
        reasoning_effort: 'none', // IMPORTANT: 'none' = non-think mode (fast, cheap); 'high'/'max' = reasoning (expensive). Default is 'high' — always set this explicitly
      },
    },
  });
  console.log(content);
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof MindStudioError) {
    console.error(err.code, err.status, err.message);
  }
  throw err;
}
```

### Option C — DeepSeek V4 Pro with reasoning enabled (when you need it)
```typescript
import { mindstudio, MindStudioError } from '@mindstudio-ai/agent';

try {
  const { content } = await mindstudio.generateText({
    message: 'Solve this complex problem...',
    modelOverride: {
      model: 'deepseek-v4-pro',
      temperature: 0.7,
      maxResponseTokens: 32000, // do not reduce — reasoning tokens count against this; lowering truncates the thinking chain and corrupts output
      config: {
        reasoning_effort: 'high', // 'high' or 'max' for complex tasks; this is also the model default
        top_p: 0.95,              // nucleus sampling, default 0.95
        // seed: 42,              // optional: set for reproducibility
      },
    },
  });
  console.log(content);
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof MindStudioError) {
    console.error(err.code, err.status, err.message);
  }
  throw err;
}
```

---

## Config reference for V4 Pro / V4 Flash

| Key | Type | Default | Range | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `reasoning_effort` | enum | `"high"` | `"none"` / `"high"` / `"max"` | **Set to `"none"` to disable thinking and cut costs** |
| `top_p` | number | `0.95` | `0–1` | Nucleus sampling |
| `top_k` | number | `20` | `0–100` | Top-k sampling (0 = disabled) |
| `min_p` | number | `0` | `0–1` | Min probability threshold |
| `presence_penalty` | number | `0` | `-2–2` | Discourage topic repetition |
| `frequency_penalty` | number | `0` | `-2–2` | Discourage token repetition |
| `repetition_penalty` | number | `1` | `0–2` | >1 discourages repeats |
| `seed` | number | — | `-1–2147483647` | Reproducibility |

**Bottom line:** If your primary goal is cost reduction, `deepseek-v3-1` is the right swap — no reasoning overhead, highest platform usage of any DeepSeek model, and a drop-in replacement. Only reach for V4 Pro if you specifically need the 384k context window or controllable reasoning.

